<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="387" pageId="5" pageNumber="386" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1925,2024]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1437,153,647]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="387" pageId="5" pageNumber="386">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1997,2024]" pageId="5" pageNumber="386">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The new species can be distinguished from its congeners by the following characters: 1) three cross- veins arranged in a brown line at FM 
<subScript attach="left" box="[563,589,170,184]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="387">3+4</subScript>
(
<figureCitation box="[603,693,153,180]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1213,1238]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,184,1194]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,174,1194]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Bittacus longilobus sp. n. A. Male habitus in lateral view, paratype; B. articulation of basitarsus and tibia, to show the two apical tibial spurs, holotype; C. tarsomeres IV–V, paratype; D. right wings, holotype; E. head in frontal view, holotype; F. thorax in dorsal view, paratype. Abbreviations: see Fig. 2 caption. Scale bars: A = 5 mm; B, E and F = 0.5 mm; C = 0.2 mm; D = 2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3602540" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3602540/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="387">Fig. 6D</figureCitation>
); and 2) epandrial lobe trapezoid for the main body in lateral view, with a slender elongate lobe at ventro-distal apex and a blunt process at dorso-distal apex; the lobe roughly one-third as wide as and twice as long as the main epandrial lobe (
<figureCitation box="[785,875,225,251]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1417,1442]" captionTargetBox="[151,1321,207,1398]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1328,174,1398]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Bittacus longilobus sp. n. A. Male terminalia in lateral view, holotype; B. male terminalia in dorsal view, holotype; C. female terminalia in lateral view, paratype; D. female terminalia in ventral view, paratype. Abbreviations: see Fig. 3 caption. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3602542" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3602542/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="387">Fig. 7A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="387" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,153,647]" pageId="6" pageNumber="387">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,261,287]" pageId="6" pageNumber="387">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zhang &amp; Du &amp; Hua" authorityYear="2020" box="[585,703,261,287]" class="Insecta" family="Bittacidae" genus="Bittacus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="387" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longilobus">
<emphasis box="[585,703,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="387">longilobus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” is derived from the Latin “ 
<emphasis box="[1028,1103,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="387">longus</emphasis>
” (long) and “ 
<emphasis box="[1260,1321,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="387">lobus</emphasis>
” (a lobe), referring to the long ventro-distal lobe of the male epandrium.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="388" pageId="6" pageNumber="387" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,153,647]" pageId="6" pageNumber="387">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,415,332,359]" pageId="6" pageNumber="387">
Description. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[353,415,332,359]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="387">Head</emphasis>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[431,517,333,360]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1213,1238]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,184,1194]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,174,1194]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Bittacus longilobus sp. n. A. Male habitus in lateral view, paratype; B. articulation of basitarsus and tibia, to show the two apical tibial spurs, holotype; C. tarsomeres IV–V, paratype; D. right wings, holotype; E. head in frontal view, holotype; F. thorax in dorsal view, paratype. Abbreviations: see Fig. 2 caption. Scale bars: A = 5 mm; B, E and F = 0.5 mm; C = 0.2 mm; D = 2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3602540" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3602540/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="387">Fig. 6E</figureCitation>
). Vertex yellowish brown. Ocellar triangle blackish brown. Rostrum slightly yellowish basally, brown medially and yellowish brown apically; labial and maxillary palps dark brown. Antenna filiform; scape and pedicel pale brown; flagellum blackish brown, 17-segmented.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,153,647]" pageId="6" pageNumber="387">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,285,440,467]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="387">Thorax</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[303,459,441,467]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1213,1238]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,184,1194]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,174,1194]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Bittacus longilobus sp. n. A. Male habitus in lateral view, paratype; B. articulation of basitarsus and tibia, to show the two apical tibial spurs, holotype; C. tarsomeres IV–V, paratype; D. right wings, holotype; E. head in frontal view, holotype; F. thorax in dorsal view, paratype. Abbreviations: see Fig. 2 caption. Scale bars: A = 5 mm; B, E and F = 0.5 mm; C = 0.2 mm; D = 2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3602540" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3602540/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="387">Fig. 6B, C, F</figureCitation>
). Pronotum yellowish brown, with two long setae on anterior and posterior margins. Mesonotum fuscous laterally, with a pair of black setae, scutellum light yellowish; metanotum yellowish brown laterally, light yellowish medially, scutellum pale yellowish. Legs yellowish, fuscous at apex; several short black setae on femora, tibiae and tarsi; tibia with two apical spurs, the longer one about twice as long as the shorter one in hind leg. Tarsomere IV bearing 27–31 prominent black ventral teeth and 3–4 setae on each side subbasally; tarsomere V with 30–33 ventral teeth.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3602538" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3602538" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3602538/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="387" startId="6.[151,250,1923,1948]" targetBox="[151,1435,682,1892]" targetPageId="6">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1923,2020]" pageId="6" pageNumber="387">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,278,1923,1948]" pageId="6" pageNumber="387">FIGURE 5.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Zhang &amp; Du &amp; Hua, 2020" authorityName="Zhang &amp; Du &amp; Hua" authorityYear="2020" box="[287,528,1924,1948]" class="Insecta" family="Bittacidae" genus="Bittacus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="387" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shaoguanensis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[287,528,1924,1948]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="387">Bittacus shaoguanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[537,597,1924,1948]" pageId="6" pageNumber="387">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[537,597,1924,1948]" pageId="6" pageNumber="387" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
A. Male terminalia in lateral view, holotype; B. male terminalia in dorsal view, holotype; C. female terminalia in lateral view, paratype; D. female terminalia in ventral view, paratype. Abbreviations: see Fig. 3 caption. Scale bars = 0.2 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3602540" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3602540" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3602540/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="388" startId="7.[151,250,1213,1238]" targetBox="[151,1435,184,1194]" targetPageId="7">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1213,1346]" pageId="7" pageNumber="388">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,275,1213,1238]" pageId="7" pageNumber="388">FIGURE 6.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Zhang &amp; Du &amp; Hua, 2020" authorityName="Zhang &amp; Du &amp; Hua" authorityYear="2020" box="[281,478,1214,1238]" class="Insecta" family="Bittacidae" genus="Bittacus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="388" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longilobus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[281,478,1214,1238]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="388">Bittacus longilobus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[484,541,1214,1238]" pageId="7" pageNumber="388">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[484,541,1214,1238]" pageId="7" pageNumber="388" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
A. Male habitus in lateral view, paratype; B. articulation of basitarsus and tibia, to show the two apical tibial spurs, holotype; C. tarsomeres IV–V, paratype; D. right wings, holotype; E. head in frontal view, holotype; F. thorax in dorsal view, paratype. Abbreviations: see Fig. 2 caption. Scale bars: A = 5 mm; B, E and F = 0.5 mm; C = 0.2 mm; D = 2 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1391,2030]" pageId="7" pageNumber="388">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,271,1392,1418]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="388">Wings</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[292,384,1392,1419]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1213,1238]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,184,1194]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,174,1194]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Bittacus longilobus sp. n. A. Male habitus in lateral view, paratype; B. articulation of basitarsus and tibia, to show the two apical tibial spurs, holotype; C. tarsomeres IV–V, paratype; D. right wings, holotype; E. head in frontal view, holotype; F. thorax in dorsal view, paratype. Abbreviations: see Fig. 2 caption. Scale bars: A = 5 mm; B, E and F = 0.5 mm; C = 0.2 mm; D = 2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3602540" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3602540/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="388">Fig. 6D</figureCitation>
). Wing membrane yellowish-brown. Forewing length 
<quantity box="[1026,1196,1392,1419]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0799999999999996" metricValueMax="2.17" metricValueMin="1.9899999999999998" pageId="7" pageNumber="388" unit="mm" value="20.799999999999997" valueMax="21.7" valueMin="19.9">19.9–21.7 mm</quantity>
, width 
<quantity box="[1289,1432,1391,1419]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.75" metricValueMax="5.2" metricValueMin="4.3" pageId="7" pageNumber="388" unit="mm" value="4.75" valueMax="5.2" valueMin="4.3">4.3–5.2 mm</quantity>
; pterostigma prominent; six markings, one each at OM, ORs, Scv, FRs and ends of CuA and CuP; crossveins and apical margin shaded with dark brown; thyridium conspicuous with pale border at FM; 1A terminating beyond FM; one Scv; two Pcv; no Av. Hindwing length 
<quantity box="[635,800,1500,1527]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8549999999999998" metricValueMax="1.92" metricValueMin="1.7899999999999998" pageId="7" pageNumber="388" unit="mm" value="18.549999999999997" valueMax="19.2" valueMin="17.9">17.9–19.2 mm</quantity>
, width 4.0– 
<quantity box="[932,1019,1500,1527]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.7" pageId="7" pageNumber="388" unit="mm" value="4.7">4.7 mm</quantity>
, similar to forewing.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1391,2030]" pageId="7" pageNumber="388">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,411,1535,1562]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="388">Abdomen of male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[430,534,1536,1562]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1213,1238]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,184,1194]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,174,1194]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Bittacus longilobus sp. n. A. Male habitus in lateral view, paratype; B. articulation of basitarsus and tibia, to show the two apical tibial spurs, holotype; C. tarsomeres IV–V, paratype; D. right wings, holotype; E. head in frontal view, holotype; F. thorax in dorsal view, paratype. Abbreviations: see Fig. 2 caption. Scale bars: A = 5 mm; B, E and F = 0.5 mm; C = 0.2 mm; D = 2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3602540" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3602540/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="388">Figs. 6A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[549,562,1537,1563]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1417,1442]" captionTargetBox="[151,1321,207,1398]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1328,174,1398]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Bittacus longilobus sp. n. A. Male terminalia in lateral view, holotype; B. male terminalia in dorsal view, holotype; C. female terminalia in lateral view, paratype; D. female terminalia in ventral view, paratype. Abbreviations: see Fig. 3 caption. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3602542" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3602542/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="388">7</figureCitation>
A–B). Terga II–VIII yellowish brown, each with a narrow black antecosta. Epandrial lobe yellowish, trapezoid for the main body in lateral view, with a slender elongate lobe at ventro-distal apex; the lobe roughly one-third as wide as and twice as long as the main epandrial lobe; a patch of short black thick spines on the inner surface at the dorso-distal portion of the main epandrial lobe and the subapex of the distal lobe, respectively; the distal lobe convergent distally in dorsal view. Upper branch of proctiger protruding between bases of epandrial lobe, furnished apically with long black hairs; lower branch of proctiger very short. Tergum X yellowish brown. Cerci elongate, slightly shorter than gonocoxites, but longer than the distal epandrial lobe. Gonocoxites yellowish brown, shorter than epandrial lobe; gonostylus reduced.Aedeagus expanded basally; penisfilum short and coiled approximately in apical half.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1391,2030]" pageId="7" pageNumber="388">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,423,1859,1886]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="388">Abdomen of female</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[437,502,1860,1886]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1417,1442]" captionTargetBox="[151,1321,207,1398]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1328,174,1398]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Bittacus longilobus sp. n. A. Male terminalia in lateral view, holotype; B. male terminalia in dorsal view, holotype; C. female terminalia in lateral view, paratype; D. female terminalia in ventral view, paratype. Abbreviations: see Fig. 3 caption. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3602542" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3602542/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="388">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
C–D). Terga II–VIII yellowish brown, each with a narrow black antecosta. Subgenital plate broad with a distal patch of stiff setae; yellowish brown, sclerotized and separated by a triangular median membranous area, and with an inconspicuous U-shaped distal membranous area in lateral view. Tergum X blackish brown, only slightly extending ventrally. Supraanal plate shorter than subanal plate, truncate apically. Cerci slightly shorter than subanal plate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
